      • FREEZE_TIMEOUT_DEFAULT

        public static final int FREEZE_TIMEOUT_DEFAULT
        The freeze timeout is the time after which the recognition cannot be modified. This can be used to gather a lot of recognitions together.
        Time set in milliseconds. The minimum value is from 200 to 10000 ms. This is used in the configure() method.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • configure

        public Error configure(String locale,
              List<String> resources,
              List<String> lexicon,
              byte[] bytes,
              float dpi,
              int freezeTimeout)
        Configures the handwriting recognition engine.


        This function is non-blocking and returns immediately. Configuration is a lengthy process that may take up to
        several seconds, depending on the handwriting resources to be configured. It is recommended to setup a configure
        listener to detect the end of the configuration process.

        Parameters:
        locale - String representation of the handwriting recognition locale.
        resources - Array of paths to handwriting resource files.
        lexicon - Array of user lexicon entries. May be null.
        dpi - The coordinate resolution in dot per inch.
        freezeTimeout - The minimum freeze time before the launch of the recognition.
        It corresponds to the time between the last request and the launch of the recognition. Can be from 200 to 10000 ms. The default value is 650 ms.

        Returns:

        UnsuitableConfig if the freezeTimeout value is invalid
        PageInterpreterOverflow if the maximum number of configured PageInterpreter is reached
        NoError otherwise

      • saveConfiguration

        public String saveConfiguration()
        Saves the configuration of the recognition. The same configuration can then be reused on another wrapper after the
        original one was deleted or reconfigured. If called before the configuration, an empty String will be returned.

        Warning: If you don't call restoreConfigurationFromId after, there will be a memory leak.
        Returns:
        The id of the save of the configuration, or an empty String if no configuration

      • setGuidelines

        public Error setGuidelines(float firstLinePosition,
                  float gap,
                  int lineCount)
        Sets the guidelines
        The values must be absolute. Only the firstLinePosition can be equal to 0, the other ones must be greater than 0.
        Parameters:
        firstLinePosition - The position of the first guideline (>= 0)
        gap - The gap between two consecutive guidelines (> 0)
        lineCount - The number of lines showed (> 0)
        Returns:
        Error, NoError if correct value, WrongGuidelinesNumber otherwise
